WEBVTT

00:05.048 --> 00:06.397
<i>Previously on</i> <i>
"The Rookie"...</i>

00:06.441 --> 00:07.964
That's Aaron Thorsen.

00:08.008 --> 00:09.661
Rich kid.
TikTok famous

00:09.705 --> 00:12.882
before he got arrested for
murdering his roommate in Paris.

00:12.925 --> 00:16.016
I was locked in a cell
for 541 days.

00:16.059 --> 00:18.409
The person who murdered Patrick,
he's still out there,

00:18.453 --> 00:20.237
and no one is looking for him

00:20.281 --> 00:21.673
because they still think
that I did it.

00:21.717 --> 00:23.675
I don't want to be a part of
this reality TV show.

00:23.719 --> 00:25.721
Sweetie, it's only
gonna help you.

00:25.764 --> 00:28.376
I'm Morris Mackey. I'm
the reality TV producer here.

00:28.419 --> 00:30.552
I just want to say,
this has been so fascinating.

00:30.595 --> 00:33.250
I love true crime,
and to be in a documentary,

00:33.294 --> 00:34.817
it's just --
it's a dream come true.

00:34.860 --> 00:35.818
Thank you.
Thank you.

00:39.126 --> 00:40.779
Nolan:
Do I just...?

00:41.824 --> 00:43.217
You're back.

00:43.260 --> 00:44.261
Interviewer:
Another crazy story --

00:44.305 --> 00:47.090
- how could I stay away?
- Thank you.

00:47.134 --> 00:48.700
- You good to go?
- Um, yeah.

00:48.744 --> 00:50.180
Where should I, uh --
where should I start?

00:50.224 --> 00:52.574
Why don't you, uh, tell me
about Aaron Thorsen?

00:52.617 --> 00:55.403
Well, Aaron came
to the F.T.O. program

00:55.446 --> 00:57.361
with the deck stacked
against him.

00:57.405 --> 01:00.408
He had to sue the LAPD
even to get into the Academy.

01:00.451 --> 01:02.410
I mean, you have to respect
just how hard he fought

01:02.453 --> 01:04.238
just to be here.

01:04.281 --> 01:08.198
Uh, but what happened in Paris
never left him,

01:08.242 --> 01:10.287
no matter how hard he tried
to move on.

01:10.331 --> 01:12.072
People would argue that doing
a reality show

01:12.115 --> 01:14.161
is the opposite
of moving on.

01:14.204 --> 01:15.988
Well, those people
haven't experienced

01:16.032 --> 01:17.903
what it's like
to be infamous.

01:17.947 --> 01:21.385
I mean, Aaron was desperate to
reset the way the world saw him.

01:21.429 --> 01:22.865
And it all blew up
in his face.

01:22.908 --> 01:25.389
Yeah.
Yeah, it really did.

01:35.921 --> 01:38.141
Aaron: I can't believe this
is happening to me again.

01:38.185 --> 01:39.447
Interviewer: It's nice
to see you again.

01:39.490 --> 01:40.578
Mm-hmm.

01:40.622 --> 01:42.450
And congratulations
on the baby.

01:42.493 --> 01:43.973
Thank you.

01:44.016 --> 01:45.496
Did being pregnant
make what you went through

01:45.540 --> 01:46.541
with Aaron
more stressful?

01:46.584 --> 01:47.977
Not here to talk about me.

01:48.020 --> 01:49.848
Fair enough. Uh,
let's talk about

01:49.892 --> 01:50.893
the reality show.

01:50.936 --> 01:53.200
Okay.
It was his mom's idea.

01:53.243 --> 01:55.724
It was a way to rebrand
his image.

01:55.767 --> 01:57.204
And what did you think
of the title?

01:58.509 --> 01:59.771
No comment.

01:59.815 --> 02:01.251
Seriously, though.
You have to have

02:01.295 --> 02:03.035
had an opinion --Listen, you're not
gonna get me

02:03.079 --> 02:05.821
to say that dumbass title,
so let's just move on.

02:32.413 --> 02:34.589
Yeah, so back there
is my parents' room

02:34.632 --> 02:35.981
and the family room.

02:36.025 --> 02:39.811
Um... Oh, right here,
this is my favorite photo.

02:39.855 --> 02:41.335
I was 6.

02:41.378 --> 02:42.945
And you might recognize
my dad.

02:42.988 --> 02:45.904
He was part of a '90s rap duo,
Flex n' Flow.

02:45.948 --> 02:47.123
That's them right here.

02:47.167 --> 02:48.342
♪ Party's never stoppin'

02:48.385 --> 02:49.473
♪ Who the boys
that make the noise? ♪

02:49.517 --> 02:50.735
♪ Flex n' Flow, yo,
Flex n' Flow ♪

02:50.779 --> 02:52.041
Yeah, man, when I was a kid,
I used to love

02:52.084 --> 02:54.435
riding my tricycle up and down
this hallway.

02:54.478 --> 02:57.046
Until he knocked over my Music
Industry Achievement Award

02:57.089 --> 02:58.482
and broke it.

02:58.526 --> 03:00.397
Aaron tried to put it back
together with Play-Doh,

03:00.441 --> 03:02.443
thinking we wouldn't notice.

03:02.486 --> 03:06.011
But that's my son, always trying
to get away with something.

03:07.404 --> 03:08.753
Not anymore.

03:08.797 --> 03:11.756
I mean, now he's...
very responsible.

03:13.410 --> 03:15.586
Over here, we got
my childhood bedroom.

03:18.502 --> 03:21.026
What the hell?

03:21.070 --> 03:23.594
Hey, I never had
this picture of Patrick.

03:23.638 --> 03:24.943
Did you put this here?

03:24.987 --> 03:26.989
Morris: We just thought it'd be
a nice surprise.

03:27.032 --> 03:28.251
Man, Morris, what the hell
did I tell you, man,

03:28.295 --> 03:29.774
about faking stuff like this?

03:29.818 --> 03:31.907
Relax.
Uh, not a big deal.

03:31.950 --> 03:33.865
We just wanted to do it
for a take.

03:33.909 --> 03:34.779
Yeah, man,
that's not cool.

03:34.823 --> 03:35.824
You know what?
You're right.

03:35.867 --> 03:37.260
My bad.

03:37.304 --> 03:40.045
We'll -- We'll do it again,
but without the photo.

03:40.089 --> 03:41.351
Okay.

03:41.395 --> 03:43.135
Yeah, okay.

03:46.313 --> 03:47.966
Got that?

03:48.010 --> 03:50.012
Morris was white-hot
from doing

03:50.055 --> 03:52.057
several award-winning
documentaries in a row.

03:52.101 --> 03:54.146
The king of those
"30 Under 30" lists.

03:54.190 --> 03:56.236
He had a real gift
for earning people's trust,

03:56.279 --> 03:58.281
convincing them
that he was on their side,

03:58.325 --> 04:00.849
that they have a say
on the final cut.

04:00.892 --> 04:02.807
Then -- surprise --
they didn't.

04:05.941 --> 04:07.377
Hey.

04:07.421 --> 04:10.075
Sorry. I, uh, totally forgot
this was happening today.

04:10.119 --> 04:11.294
We just started.

04:11.338 --> 04:12.643
Uh, don't forget to tell him
about the, uh,

04:12.687 --> 04:13.688
forensics expert.

04:13.731 --> 04:14.950
I know.

04:14.993 --> 04:16.691
And the, uh --
the French prosecutor.

04:16.734 --> 04:17.953
I sent you that interview,
right?

04:17.996 --> 04:19.607
He was biased against Aaron
from the jump.

04:21.261 --> 04:23.306
I'm a decade older,

04:23.350 --> 04:25.221
but Aaron and I
had similar upbringings --

04:25.265 --> 04:27.223
rich parents,
private schools.

04:27.267 --> 04:29.617
I'm just lucky social media
didn't exist.

04:29.660 --> 04:31.227
Look, if I was
in Aaron's generation,

04:31.271 --> 04:33.490
I would have just as much
embarrassing footage as he did.

04:33.534 --> 04:36.493
Of what?
You studying tort reform at 15?

04:36.537 --> 04:38.452
I got into trouble.

04:38.495 --> 04:39.931
- Uh-huh.
- Okay.

04:39.975 --> 04:41.933
The point is, when you grow up
in this world,

04:41.977 --> 04:44.414
you don't hear "no" a lot,
which can make you a real ass--

04:44.458 --> 04:46.155
can make you
a very selfish person.

04:46.198 --> 04:47.374
♪ Another day

04:47.417 --> 04:49.071
Aaron: Ooh-hoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

04:49.114 --> 04:50.725
Yo, they only got,
like, five pairs of these

04:50.768 --> 04:52.509
in the whole world,
and I got a pair.

04:52.553 --> 04:53.771
You don't have a pair,
but I do.

04:53.815 --> 04:55.773
What's up, what's up?!

04:55.817 --> 04:56.513
Hey, yo, what up,
everybody?

04:56.557 --> 04:57.688
It's your boy, AT!

04:57.732 --> 04:59.473
My guy Patty P right here.

04:59.516 --> 05:02.824
We got a pool party tonight.
Everybody come through.

05:02.867 --> 05:04.434
Got the matching,
you know?

05:04.478 --> 05:05.870
- Got the matching.
- And the shoes.

05:05.914 --> 05:07.481
Hey.
Have fun.

05:07.524 --> 05:09.091
- You know what it is.
- Hey! Whoa!

05:09.134 --> 05:10.614
You know the vibes.

05:10.658 --> 05:11.615
You know the vibes!

05:16.707 --> 05:19.014
$30,000 a bottle,

05:19.057 --> 05:20.494
and he didn't drink a sip.

05:20.537 --> 05:22.887
That boy lost his mind.

05:22.931 --> 05:24.585
I had to get him out
of his comfort zone.

05:24.628 --> 05:26.848
I mean, I-I thought, you know,
a semester abroad

05:26.891 --> 05:28.371
would've helped him mature,

05:28.415 --> 05:30.721
so I sent him to Paris.

05:36.684 --> 05:38.642
<i>I was on scholarship.</i>

05:38.686 --> 05:40.035
University of Michigan.

05:40.078 --> 05:41.732
Go Wolverines.

05:41.776 --> 05:43.647
I don't know why I said that.
Can I please start over?

05:43.691 --> 05:46.128
Interviewer:
You're doing fine.

05:46.171 --> 05:47.999
Uh, when did you first meet
Aaron and Patrick?

05:48.043 --> 05:50.393
The program held a mixer
when we first arrived.

05:50.437 --> 05:52.526
It was mostly just a bunch of
awkward college students

05:52.569 --> 05:54.310
butchering French,

05:54.354 --> 05:56.834
but Aaron and Patrick were from
this whole other world.

05:56.878 --> 05:59.010
First impressions?

05:59.054 --> 06:03.188
I mean, honestly, they seemed
like entitled douchebags.

06:03.232 --> 06:04.364
But then I got to know them.

06:04.407 --> 06:06.278
You know,
it was like another planet --

06:06.322 --> 06:07.671
Planet Rich.

06:07.715 --> 06:09.151
Patrick was the funniest.

06:09.194 --> 06:11.283
All that stuff you saw
on Instagram,

06:11.327 --> 06:12.807
no, that's not who they were.

06:12.850 --> 06:14.852
Yeah, I mean, we went from
the Two Musketeers to Four,

06:14.896 --> 06:16.158
you know, just like that.

06:16.201 --> 06:18.160
Me, Patrick,
Rowan, and Everest,

06:18.203 --> 06:22.033
we were, uh, inseparable.

06:22.077 --> 06:24.296
And uh...

06:24.340 --> 06:26.473
Man, that feels like
so long ago.

06:26.516 --> 06:27.648
Are you nervous about
the reunion?

06:27.691 --> 06:28.866
A little.

06:28.910 --> 06:31.129
Or a lot.

06:31.173 --> 06:34.742
Yeah, I mean, um, I haven't seen
them since the trial.

06:34.785 --> 06:37.527
And they all went home,
graduated from college,

06:37.571 --> 06:39.660
got jobs, and...

06:39.703 --> 06:41.096
I went to prison.

06:41.139 --> 06:42.402
Do they believe
in your innocence?

06:42.445 --> 06:44.229
Yeah, 100%.

06:44.273 --> 06:45.361
They've both said that.

06:45.405 --> 06:46.623
You know, there can be
a big difference

06:46.667 --> 06:49.278
between what people say
and what they believe.

06:52.760 --> 06:53.978
Sorry. Let's --
Hold on.

06:54.022 --> 06:56.285
Let me reset that.

06:56.328 --> 07:02.683
Sorry.

07:06.034 --> 07:08.297
Ro, Ro,
good to see you, man!

07:08.340 --> 07:09.298
Yeah, you too, man.

07:09.341 --> 07:10.560
Yeah.
You look so different.

07:10.604 --> 07:12.083
Yeah, I'm a little older.

07:12.127 --> 07:14.172
No, it's not that.
I don't know.

07:14.216 --> 07:15.565
You're like
a different guy.

07:15.609 --> 07:17.480
Something like that.

07:17.524 --> 07:18.916
I think I'm gonna cry. Hey.

07:18.960 --> 07:20.440
No, no, no crying.
You're gonna mess up my makeup.

07:20.483 --> 07:21.658
Oh!

07:21.702 --> 07:23.486
Oh, I'm sorry
I didn't come sooner.

07:23.530 --> 07:24.835
No, d-- don't worry about it, really.

07:24.879 --> 07:27.447
I'm just glad
to see you guys.

07:27.490 --> 07:29.187
Alright, so let's,
uh, get inside.

07:29.231 --> 07:31.451
I got food, drinks...

07:31.494 --> 07:34.018
cameras, and, uh...

07:34.062 --> 07:35.846
I'm sorry.
This is so weird.

07:35.890 --> 07:37.326
Hey, it's fine. We're just happy
to see you, bro.

07:38.458 --> 07:39.589
Yeah, me too. Yeah.

07:39.633 --> 07:41.243
Yeah. Alright.

07:41.286 --> 07:42.374
Connor: Guys, I got to swap out
my battery.

07:42.418 --> 07:43.854
Give me a second?

07:43.898 --> 07:45.508
Aaron: Okay.

07:53.342 --> 07:54.561
What the hell?

08:04.353 --> 08:05.876
Holy -

08:05.920 --> 08:07.530
Morris Mackey's throat
had been cut.

08:07.574 --> 08:08.923
By the time
his body was found,

08:08.966 --> 08:10.968
he'd been dead approximately
four hours.

08:11.012 --> 08:12.796
Interviewer: And who were
your initial suspects?

08:12.840 --> 08:14.319
Everyone who stepped foot
in the house that day.

08:14.363 --> 08:15.320
Including Aaron.

08:15.364 --> 08:16.931
Everyone.

08:16.974 --> 08:19.629
- Interviewer: Good morning.
- Good morning.

08:19.673 --> 08:20.412
It's nice to see you again.

08:20.456 --> 08:22.153
Nice to see you!

08:22.197 --> 08:23.154
I heard you were happy
with how

08:23.198 --> 08:24.373
the last documentary
came out.

08:24.416 --> 08:27.028
Oh, my God.
It was so good, and -- and --

08:27.071 --> 08:29.596
And I got so many compliments.

08:29.639 --> 08:32.729
Oh, that's great.
How about you?

08:32.773 --> 08:34.557
Didn't see it.
Can we get started?

08:34.601 --> 08:36.211
Uh, yeah.

08:36.254 --> 08:38.474
So, tell me what happened when
you arrived at the scene.

08:38.518 --> 08:39.562
We were
the first responders.

08:46.787 --> 08:47.962
Lucy: Whoa.

08:48.005 --> 08:48.963
Okay.

08:49.006 --> 08:51.182
It was a...frenetic day.

08:51.226 --> 08:55.578
So many people -- so --
so many personalities.

08:55.622 --> 08:58.015
But when you're talking
a star-studded crime scene

08:58.059 --> 09:01.410
with a witness list comprised
mostly of influencers,

09:01.453 --> 09:03.107
I guess that's
no surprise.

09:03.151 --> 09:04.631
Alright, look,
even with all those cameras

09:04.674 --> 09:07.111
and phones rolling in the house,
none of them caught anything

09:07.155 --> 09:08.809
even remotely helpful
to our investigation.

09:08.852 --> 09:10.332
Yeah. Luck?

09:10.375 --> 09:12.987
It just wasn't in our cards
that day.

09:14.554 --> 09:15.555
What?
Why are you so happy?

09:15.598 --> 09:18.035
I am being colorful.

09:18.079 --> 09:19.123
They will use more
of our coverage

09:19.167 --> 09:20.560
if we give them evocative
sound bites.

09:20.603 --> 09:21.952
I'm right, right?

09:21.996 --> 09:23.867
Can we get back
to the murder?

09:23.911 --> 09:26.174
I followed protocols.
You know, I -- I called it in,

09:26.217 --> 09:27.915
cleared the house,
did everything right.

09:27.958 --> 09:29.264
- Lucy: Mm-hmm.
- You believe me, right?

09:29.307 --> 09:30.744
O-Of course.

09:30.787 --> 09:32.484
I mean, but we have to
follow protocol, too.

09:32.528 --> 09:34.225
It's gonna be okay.

09:34.269 --> 09:35.879
I can't believe this
is happening to me again.

09:35.923 --> 09:37.054
I know.

09:38.360 --> 09:41.145
A-Are you okay?

09:41.189 --> 09:42.930
I think I'm having, like,
a panic attack.

09:42.973 --> 09:44.584
Oh, okay.
Uh, just sit down,

09:44.627 --> 09:45.715
and I'm gonna grab you
some water, okay?

09:45.759 --> 09:46.977
I'll be right back.

09:47.021 --> 09:48.675
Show's over.
Time to go.

09:48.718 --> 09:51.416
What? Uh, no, no, no.
No, it's not.

09:51.460 --> 09:53.462
This is my house,
my production.

09:53.505 --> 09:54.463
The show goes on.

09:54.506 --> 09:55.638
Connor, keep filming.

09:55.682 --> 09:56.683
Yeah, that's not
how this works.

09:56.726 --> 09:57.814
This is
my crime scene.

09:57.858 --> 10:00.425
Shut it off now.

10:00.469 --> 10:01.601
Shut it off!

10:03.864 --> 10:05.039
There was nothing
we could do.

10:05.082 --> 10:06.214
Tim:
Well, thanks for coming out.

10:06.257 --> 10:07.519
Yeah.

10:07.563 --> 10:09.870
Our paramedic crew was
short-staffed,

10:09.913 --> 10:13.264
and since we're all EMT-trained,
I was subbing in.

10:13.308 --> 10:14.309
Interviewer:
Oh, I don't understand.

10:14.352 --> 10:15.527
Why were you called in
at all?

10:15.571 --> 10:17.181
He was clearly dead,
right?

10:17.225 --> 10:19.575
You have no idea how many people
I see look that way

10:19.619 --> 10:21.185
and then spring back to life.

10:21.229 --> 10:22.796
Oh. Interesting.

10:22.839 --> 10:24.101
And what did you think
at the time?

10:24.145 --> 10:25.668
Did it seem to you
like Aaron did it?

10:25.712 --> 10:28.410
Of course not. He would never do
anything like that.

10:28.453 --> 10:30.586
Really? And you're confident
saying that --

10:30.630 --> 10:33.197
considering
your ex-husband?

10:33.241 --> 10:36.679
Wow. Okay.

10:36.723 --> 10:38.289
Ah, clearly,
you come prepared.

10:38.333 --> 10:43.207
Yeah, um, I --
I married a sociopath once.

10:43.251 --> 10:46.297
So maybe I'm not
the best judge of character.

10:46.341 --> 10:47.647
It's not about being
a good judge of character.

10:47.690 --> 10:49.126
We judge by the facts.

10:49.170 --> 10:50.693
Interviewer:
And what did the facts say?

10:50.737 --> 10:52.652
At first?

10:52.695 --> 10:53.914
Not much.

10:56.003 --> 10:57.744
How long you been here
filming today?

10:57.787 --> 10:59.441
About three
or four hours.

10:59.484 --> 11:00.616
After rehearsal
this morning,

11:00.660 --> 11:02.009
they had Everest and me
in the kitchen,

11:02.052 --> 11:03.532
getting our hair
and makeup done

11:03.575 --> 11:05.012
while they filmed
other stuff.

11:05.055 --> 11:06.491
Lucy: So you were in the kitchen
the whole time?

11:06.535 --> 11:10.234
Uh, well, I did sneak off
to crafty once or...

11:10.278 --> 11:11.714
four times.
I heard they had ice cream,

11:11.758 --> 11:12.976
and I've been dieting
like crazy

11:13.020 --> 11:14.238
'cause I was gonna be
on television,

11:14.282 --> 11:15.762
and I heard the camera
adds like 10 pounds.

11:15.805 --> 11:17.328
Is that true?

11:17.372 --> 11:18.982
Tim: So when was the last time
you saw Morris?

11:19.026 --> 11:20.810
Honestly, I ain't seen him
all day.

11:20.854 --> 11:22.116
I was dealing with work stuff

11:22.159 --> 11:23.900
right up
until we started filming.

11:23.944 --> 11:25.946
Lucy: And where were you
when Morris's body was found?

11:25.989 --> 11:27.904
In my office.

11:27.948 --> 11:29.079
And how would
you characterize

11:29.123 --> 11:31.342
Aaron's relationship
with Morris?

11:34.345 --> 11:35.956
It's important
you tell the truth.

11:38.175 --> 11:40.525
They didn't always agree about
the direction of the show.

11:40.569 --> 11:42.310
But my son,
he would never hurt anyone.

11:49.665 --> 11:52.450
Hey, do we really have
to do this in here?

11:52.494 --> 11:53.713
Yes, we do, son.

11:55.802 --> 11:58.718
Per government code 3300
and per Lybarger,

11:58.761 --> 12:01.198
I am required to advise
that you do <i>not</i> have

12:01.242 --> 12:02.852
the right
to remain silent.

12:02.896 --> 12:05.550
Anything you say can
and will be used against you.

12:05.594 --> 12:08.379
Refusal to fully
and completely answer

12:08.423 --> 12:11.078
all of Detective Lopez's
questions

12:11.121 --> 12:14.516
will result
in immediate termination.

12:14.559 --> 12:17.693
Do you understand?

12:17.737 --> 12:18.781
Yes, sir.

12:18.825 --> 12:20.087
And I'm here
to protect you

12:20.130 --> 12:21.828
as your union representative.

12:21.871 --> 12:23.612
This is your choice.

12:23.655 --> 12:25.570
But like
Sergeant Grey said,

12:25.614 --> 12:27.790
if you choose not to cooperate,
you will lose your job.

12:27.834 --> 12:28.965
Of course I'll cooperate.

12:31.272 --> 12:32.229
Good man.

12:34.492 --> 12:35.711
Alright.

12:35.755 --> 12:36.799
I'll leave you to it.

12:40.716 --> 12:41.848
I didn't kill Morris.

12:46.113 --> 12:49.986
When I saw him lying there,
like Patrick...

12:50.030 --> 12:51.379
Lopez: I understand.

12:51.422 --> 12:53.120
But it was common knowledge
that you and Morris

12:53.163 --> 12:54.730
weren't on
the best of terms.

12:54.774 --> 12:58.125
Who are you with? TMZ?

12:58.168 --> 12:59.735
You still feeding off my grief,
- you vultures?!
- Come on, guys.

12:59.779 --> 13:00.736
Morris,
- what are you doing, man?
- Get 'em out of here, man!

13:00.780 --> 13:02.738
Get out of here now!
Go!

13:02.782 --> 13:04.827
Yeah, what he did
to Patrick's dad

13:04.871 --> 13:08.570
was callous and exploitative,

13:08.613 --> 13:10.398
but I wouldn't kill him
for it.

13:10.441 --> 13:11.834
Harper: Yeah, that was bad.

13:11.878 --> 13:15.359
Aaron pulled over Patrick's dad
in a routine car stop.

13:15.403 --> 13:17.884
It was
a total random reunion,

13:17.927 --> 13:21.322
but Morris and his cameraman
were there filming,

13:21.365 --> 13:23.672
and that just made
everything worse.

13:23.715 --> 13:27.067
Dexter Hayes, he was a --
a grieving father, you know?

13:27.110 --> 13:31.027
And he -- he took a swing
at Officer Thorsen,

13:31.071 --> 13:32.159
so we had to book him,

13:32.202 --> 13:35.205
but we let him go
as soon as we could.

13:35.249 --> 13:37.599
And, you know, I thought
that would be the end of it.

13:37.642 --> 13:38.861
Interviewer: But you suspected
that Patrick's dad

13:38.905 --> 13:41.081
- could have killed Morris?
- We did.

13:41.124 --> 13:44.084
He was furious
about "Every Rose Has A --"

13:44.127 --> 13:46.347
about the reality show.

13:46.390 --> 13:49.916
And after years of the press
feeding off of his grief,

13:49.959 --> 13:52.832
yeah, it was believable
that he could've snapped.

13:52.875 --> 13:54.964
This is absurd.
You do know that?

13:55.008 --> 13:55.878
Tim: Alright, sir,
can you tell me where you were

13:55.922 --> 13:57.314
yesterday afternoon?

13:57.358 --> 13:59.882
I was in the office,
morning to midnight.

13:59.926 --> 14:01.884
Ask any one
of my employees.

14:01.928 --> 14:03.625
I didn't do this.

14:03.668 --> 14:05.627
Any idea who did?

14:05.670 --> 14:08.717
I can tell you that
whoever killed that man,

14:08.760 --> 14:11.851
his last name is Thorsen.

14:11.894 --> 14:14.679
I blame myself for ever letting
them into Patrick's life.

14:14.723 --> 14:16.029
They're a sick family.

14:16.072 --> 14:18.466
And Aaron is not
the only killer among them.

14:18.509 --> 14:19.771
Interviewer:
What did he mean by that?

14:19.815 --> 14:20.990
You know
what he meant by that.

14:21.034 --> 14:23.384
And we knew
from the reality show

14:23.427 --> 14:25.908
that Morris gave
Aaron's father a clear motive.

14:25.952 --> 14:28.563
And that's what I was thinking
for the opening theme.

14:28.606 --> 14:29.520
Yeah?
Yeah.

14:29.564 --> 14:30.260
I like it.

14:30.304 --> 14:31.827
You do?

14:31.871 --> 14:33.437
Almost as much
as I like you.

14:33.481 --> 14:34.961
Mm.

14:35.004 --> 14:36.919
You're so sweet.

14:36.963 --> 14:38.399
Oh.

14:38.442 --> 14:39.530
Lincoln: Hey!

14:39.574 --> 14:41.663
You hooking up
with my wife, man?!

14:41.706 --> 14:42.925
Linc,
it's not what you think.

14:42.969 --> 14:45.449
Boy, you better get
the hell up out of here!

14:48.191 --> 14:49.845
What the hell was that?!

14:49.889 --> 14:51.978
Are you seriously doing this
to me again?!

14:52.021 --> 14:53.457
In my own house!

14:53.501 --> 14:54.894
Interview: There's footage
of Lincoln catching

14:54.937 --> 14:56.765
Morris and Yvonne
in an intimate moment.

14:56.808 --> 14:58.941
That had to factor
into your investigation.

14:58.985 --> 15:01.248
Jealousy is
a primal motive.

15:01.291 --> 15:02.640
And some believe
that Lincoln had killed

15:02.684 --> 15:04.164
for jealousy
once before.

15:04.207 --> 15:06.470
He was a suspect in
a 20-year-old murder, wasn't he?

15:06.514 --> 15:07.471
Yes, he was.

15:13.869 --> 15:17.003
Interviewer: What can you
tell me about your father's
hip-hop duo, Flex n' Flow?

15:17.046 --> 15:17.960
I mean, I was, like, a baby,
you know,

15:18.004 --> 15:19.527
when they were
at their height.

15:19.570 --> 15:22.399
And, uh, that was the year
"Make Da Noise" went platinum.

15:22.443 --> 15:23.400
Interviewer: Flex n' Flow
had one of the most

15:23.444 --> 15:24.967
iconic singles
of the late '90s.

15:25.011 --> 15:26.360
Oh, my God.
"Make Da Noise"?

15:26.403 --> 15:29.450
That's like one
of my go-to karaoke jams.

15:29.493 --> 15:31.017
♪ My crib,
it's all a-poppin' ♪

15:31.060 --> 15:32.192
♪ The party's
never stoppin' ♪

15:32.235 --> 15:33.367
♪ Who da boyz that
make da noise? ♪

15:33.410 --> 15:35.543
♪ Flex 'n Flow, yo,
Flex n' Flow ♪

15:35.586 --> 15:36.544
Can I be interviewed
alone?

15:38.676 --> 15:39.982
Yeah, we comin' for you.

