15:48.991 --> 15:50.123
♪ Flex n' Flow, yo,
Flex n' Flow ♪

15:50.166 --> 15:51.254
♪ Flex n' Flow

16:00.524 --> 16:02.613
Oh, yes, that's me.

16:02.657 --> 16:05.094
I was a Flow Girl.

16:05.138 --> 16:06.922
Wait. What?

16:06.966 --> 16:09.794
There was a scout who saw me
cheering in high school,

16:09.838 --> 16:11.492
and he asked me to audition.

16:11.535 --> 16:13.842
At first, I thought he was
just trying to get in my pants.

16:13.885 --> 16:19.108
But it turned out to be legit,
and it was for Flex n' Flow.

16:19.152 --> 16:21.154
I was the biggest fan.

16:21.197 --> 16:22.459
Interviewer: What are you
wearing, by the way?

16:22.503 --> 16:25.810
Oh, I teach capoeira
on Thursdays and Sundays.

16:25.854 --> 16:26.986
Oh.

16:27.029 --> 16:28.726
Did you ever see
Flex n' Flow argue

16:28.770 --> 16:29.640
while you were working
with them?

16:29.684 --> 16:32.339
Mm, I mean...well, sure,

16:32.382 --> 16:34.167
but nothing serious.

16:34.210 --> 16:36.082
They were like brothers,
and brothers fight.

16:36.125 --> 16:37.518
What do you say to the people
who are convinced

16:37.561 --> 16:39.389
that your husband
killed his late partner?

16:39.433 --> 16:42.392
Oh, honey, this alleged "feud"
between Linc and Calvin

16:42.436 --> 16:45.265
has gotten blown way out
of proportion over the years.

16:45.308 --> 16:47.223
But what about the night
of Calvin's murder?

16:47.267 --> 16:49.399
The infamous pre-release party
for "2 Hype Homies"?

16:49.443 --> 16:52.054
Did the party
get a little wild? Sure.

16:52.098 --> 16:54.274
Did the police come
and break it up? Mm-hmm.

16:54.317 --> 16:57.059
And did Linc and Calvin argue?
You bet.

16:57.103 --> 16:59.105
But they were just
passionate people.

16:59.148 --> 17:02.238
And nobody
ever threatened nobody.

17:02.282 --> 17:05.589
Yeah, they, uh --
they threatened each other.

17:05.633 --> 17:06.764
I was there.

17:06.808 --> 17:08.418
I was a rookie officer then.

17:08.462 --> 17:11.204
And my T.O. and I had got
a 415 call

17:11.247 --> 17:13.684
for an out-of-control party.

17:13.728 --> 17:17.558
It was a record release event
for Flex n' Flow.

17:17.601 --> 17:20.082
But anyway,
as we were breaking things up,

17:20.126 --> 17:22.432
I saw Flex n' Flow
in each other's faces.

17:22.476 --> 17:24.086
Interviewer: Could you hear
what they were fighting about?

17:24.130 --> 17:27.307
No. Um, as I approached,
their limousine was pulling up.

17:27.350 --> 17:29.178
But Flex -- um --

17:29.222 --> 17:31.833
um, I'm sorry, Lincoln --
was still very hot.

17:31.876 --> 17:36.533
He refused to get into the limo
with Flow, and, um...

17:36.577 --> 17:39.014
Yeah, he said
that he'd rather walk

17:39.058 --> 17:41.277
than to deal
with Flow's nonsense.

17:41.321 --> 17:42.539
Um...

17:42.583 --> 17:44.541
It was a good thing, too.

17:44.585 --> 17:46.804
Anchor: A devastating loss
for the music industry today,

17:46.848 --> 17:50.808
as Calvin Yard, one half
of the popular duo Flex n' Flow,

17:50.852 --> 17:53.159
was gunned down in Los Angeles
last night

17:53.202 --> 17:55.683
after leaving
his record launch party.

17:55.726 --> 17:57.598
It couldn't have been
more than five minutes later

17:57.641 --> 18:00.122
that we got
a shots-fired call.

18:00.166 --> 18:04.561
As Flow's limo was making
the turn on La Cienega,

18:04.605 --> 18:07.956
a car pulled alongside it
and unloaded 20 rounds

18:07.999 --> 18:09.436
at the rear of the vehicle.

18:10.915 --> 18:13.440
Um, Flow was shot
seven times.

18:14.919 --> 18:17.183
Yeah.

18:17.226 --> 18:19.402
That was my first homicide.

18:19.446 --> 18:20.925
I'll never forget it.

18:20.969 --> 18:22.840
It changes you.

18:22.884 --> 18:27.149
I did not have anything to do
with Calvin's death.

18:27.193 --> 18:28.629
Interviewer: But at the time of
his murder, all the talk was --

18:28.672 --> 18:29.934
That was garbage, man.

18:29.978 --> 18:31.153
All garbage.

18:31.197 --> 18:32.328
I loved Calvin
like a brother.

18:32.372 --> 18:34.330
You know, this --

18:34.374 --> 18:35.897
this is
straight-up exploitive.

18:35.940 --> 18:38.856
Calvin's murder was solved
decades ago, and you know it.

18:38.900 --> 18:42.295
A man named Gary Brown
was convicted of Flow's murder.

18:42.338 --> 18:44.775
It turns out Flow
was sleeping with Gary's wife.

18:44.819 --> 18:48.257
So as far as the LAPD
was concerned, case closed.

18:48.301 --> 18:50.651
Yeah, but the aura of guilt
haunted Lincoln's reputation

18:50.694 --> 18:52.783
like a dark shroud.

18:52.827 --> 18:53.915
I'm sorry.

18:53.958 --> 18:56.265
That was really good.

18:56.309 --> 18:58.180
Thanks.

18:58.224 --> 19:00.095
And with Lincoln alibi'd out,
you know,

19:00.139 --> 19:02.358
the investigation
focused on Yvonne.

19:02.402 --> 19:04.447
Mrs. Thorsen, how long
had you been having an affair

19:04.491 --> 19:05.361
with Morris Mackey?

19:05.405 --> 19:06.797
Please.

19:06.841 --> 19:08.451
I was not sleeping
with him.

19:08.495 --> 19:11.019
But the footage -- from
"Every Rose Has A Thorsen" --

19:11.062 --> 19:13.587
- we saw it.
- That was for the show.

19:13.630 --> 19:15.371
What, are you saying
you staged it?

19:15.415 --> 19:18.635
It's a reality show.
Of course we staged it.

19:18.679 --> 19:20.681
I can prove it.
I have the rest of the footage.

19:20.724 --> 19:22.900
Boy, you better get
the hell up out of here!

19:25.686 --> 19:27.122
What the hell was that?!

19:27.166 --> 19:29.472
Are you seriously doing this
to me again?!

19:29.516 --> 19:30.473
In my own house!

19:30.517 --> 19:32.823
You got some nerve!

19:32.867 --> 19:34.651
L-Let's talk about all the women
you slept with

19:34.695 --> 19:36.436
when you were F-Flex?

19:36.479 --> 19:38.438
Morris: Cut!

19:38.481 --> 19:40.440
Cut, cut, cut, cut.

19:40.483 --> 19:43.791
Linc, buddy,
you're going off-script.

19:43.834 --> 19:44.966
"I can't believe
you're seriously

19:45.009 --> 19:46.272
doing this to me <i>again"?</i>

19:46.315 --> 19:47.882
That's not the line.

19:47.925 --> 19:49.318
Yeah, man,
I was improv'ing a little.

19:49.362 --> 19:51.190
Yeah, maybe not do that,
okay?

19:51.233 --> 19:52.843
It's a lot more powerful
if this is the first time

19:52.887 --> 19:54.236
Yvonne has stepped out
on you.

19:54.280 --> 19:56.238
Okay.
So, Morris, how did I do?

19:56.282 --> 19:57.892
It was a bit big.

19:57.935 --> 19:59.807
Yeah, maybe, uh,
dial it back a hair.

19:59.850 --> 20:01.025
Let's go again.

20:01.069 --> 20:02.636
Man: <i>Back to one.</i>

20:02.679 --> 20:03.898
Go.

20:03.941 --> 20:04.986
We're making a show, people.

20:06.901 --> 20:09.556
None of that was in the footage
you turned over to us.

20:09.599 --> 20:11.210
Oops. My bad.

20:11.253 --> 20:13.516
We want everything --
now --

20:13.560 --> 20:15.518
or you'll be arrested
for obstruction.

20:15.562 --> 20:17.999
Ooh, that was good.

20:18.042 --> 20:20.001
Do you think I can get
a copy of that?

20:20.044 --> 20:22.003
That will play really well
in the show.

20:22.046 --> 20:23.700
Mrs. Thorsen,
this is serious.

20:23.744 --> 20:25.528
Morris Mackey was murdered
in your house.

20:25.572 --> 20:27.095
Your son
is still a suspect.

20:27.138 --> 20:29.140
Just like the police
to only focus

20:29.184 --> 20:31.273
on what's
in front of their nose.

20:31.317 --> 20:33.928
Morris Mackey didn't just appear
out of thin air

20:33.971 --> 20:35.408
when he started working
for me.

20:35.451 --> 20:37.975
Honey,
the man had enemies.

20:43.198 --> 20:44.634
They're the crazy ones!

20:44.678 --> 20:46.157
We're the sane ones!

20:46.201 --> 20:48.290
You're the cult!
You're sheep!

20:48.334 --> 20:50.423
Prior to working
with the Thorsen family,

20:50.466 --> 20:53.948
Morris had been hired by a bunch
of QAnon conspiracy theorists.

20:53.991 --> 20:55.950
Apparently, they didn't like
the negative publicity

20:55.993 --> 20:57.212
they were getting,

20:57.256 --> 20:59.258
and they wanted
to show their side.

20:59.301 --> 21:00.476
Try to control
the narrative.

21:00.520 --> 21:01.738
- Mm.
- Interviewer: So what happened?

21:01.782 --> 21:03.697
Morris was allowed
into the inner sanctum.

21:03.740 --> 21:06.439
Conducted dozens of interviews
with founders and followers.

21:06.482 --> 21:08.484
But he didn't make
a propaganda film,

21:08.528 --> 21:09.790
he told the truth.

21:09.833 --> 21:11.052
We're in a war.

21:11.095 --> 21:12.793
Every one of us is prepared
to start killing

21:12.836 --> 21:13.968
for our freedom.

21:14.011 --> 21:15.143
Morris may have won
an Emmy,

21:15.186 --> 21:16.797
but he also pissed off
a lot of unhinged

21:16.840 --> 21:18.538
and hyper-violent people.

21:18.581 --> 21:20.148
The storm is coming.

21:20.191 --> 21:20.801
There will be retribution.

21:25.066 --> 21:28.504
Interviewer: I've heard rumors
that you have insight into
the QAnon angle on this case.

21:28.548 --> 21:30.637
Have you ever tried to put
toothpaste back in the tube?

21:30.680 --> 21:32.726
Look, I know
it's an expression,

21:32.769 --> 21:35.206
but have you actually tried
to do it?

21:35.250 --> 21:36.773
I have.

21:36.817 --> 21:38.601
It's basically impossible.

21:38.645 --> 21:40.342
And what do you think Q
is trying to tell people

21:40.386 --> 21:43.084
with his Q-Drops,
these cryptic messages?

21:43.127 --> 21:44.651
I really wasn't trying
to say anything.

21:44.694 --> 21:47.610
I was just typing, and maybe
I got a little carried away.

21:47.654 --> 21:49.177
Wait.
What did you say?

21:50.657 --> 21:54.008
Well, I guess now is as good
a time as any to reveal it.

21:56.402 --> 21:58.099
I'm Q.

21:58.142 --> 21:59.448
Smitty is Q?

21:59.492 --> 22:00.449
I'm sorry. What?

22:00.493 --> 22:02.059
- Lord, give me strength.
- What?

22:02.103 --> 22:04.627
A lot of writers
use pseudonyms.

22:04.671 --> 22:07.326
Q is my first initial, so...

22:07.369 --> 22:08.762
Hey, is my name down there?

22:10.938 --> 22:11.982
But it was an accident?

22:12.026 --> 22:14.376
He -- He didn't start it
on purpose?

22:14.420 --> 22:15.508
Interviewer:
That's what he said.

22:15.551 --> 22:16.987
Yeah,
sounds like Smitty.

22:17.031 --> 22:19.120
I was trying to start
the fan-fiction club

22:19.163 --> 22:21.731
for "This Is Us,"
and things just got out of hand.

22:21.775 --> 22:23.342
Interviewer: What the hell
does "This is Us" fanfic

22:23.385 --> 22:24.691
have to do with a cult?

22:24.734 --> 22:27.824
I mistakenly mixed cough syrup
with diet pills

22:27.868 --> 22:30.479
when I was writing
this satanic, alien story line

22:30.523 --> 22:32.612
for Jack and Rebecca.

22:32.655 --> 22:35.397
I woke up the next morning
and read it --

22:35.441 --> 22:36.746
none of it made sense.

22:36.790 --> 22:39.053
But, overnight,
I'd gotten so many followers,

22:39.096 --> 22:40.359
I just went with it.

22:40.402 --> 22:42.839
You can't put the toothpaste
back in the tube.

22:44.450 --> 22:48.149
Morris had received threats from
hundreds of QAnon followers,

22:48.192 --> 22:50.630
but when we started
investigating them,

22:50.673 --> 22:52.675
one immediately stood out.

22:52.719 --> 22:53.981
Interviewer: Tell me
about Connor Hart.

22:54.024 --> 22:55.461
What about him
got your attention?

22:55.504 --> 22:58.159
Well, he was working as a
cameraman on the reality show,

22:58.202 --> 23:00.422
so -- that.

23:01.597 --> 23:04.121
Tim: Connor,
thanks for coming down.

23:04.165 --> 23:05.514
I'm not in trouble, am I?

23:05.558 --> 23:08.604
No. We just need to clear
a few things up.

23:08.648 --> 23:10.998
I told you
everything I know.

23:11.041 --> 23:14.131
I was getting a battery,
and he was just lying there.

23:14.175 --> 23:15.655
I'm not sure
if you're aware,

23:15.698 --> 23:18.179
but it's common to run
background checks on witnesses.

23:18.222 --> 23:19.920
And when we looked into you,
we discovered

23:19.963 --> 23:21.182
that you're a member
of QAnon.

23:21.225 --> 23:22.836
No, no, no, I --

23:22.879 --> 23:24.838
I may have gone
to a political rally or two,

23:24.881 --> 23:26.230
but I'm really
not into that.

23:26.274 --> 23:27.971
I swear.

23:28.015 --> 23:29.625
We're in a war.

23:29.669 --> 23:32.498
Every one of us is prepared to
start killing for our freedom.

23:32.541 --> 23:34.064
The storm is coming.

23:34.108 --> 23:35.501
There will be retribution.

23:41.071 --> 23:43.639
So, clearly,
you are a follower of Q.

23:43.683 --> 23:44.858
Why would you work
for Morris?

23:44.901 --> 23:46.468
Honestly?

23:46.512 --> 23:47.904
I realized
Morris was the best thing

23:47.948 --> 23:49.645
that could have happened
to the movement.

23:49.689 --> 23:50.864
That makes no sense.

23:50.907 --> 23:52.692
But it does.

23:52.735 --> 23:55.477
Morris's documentary exposed
who was a true believer.

23:55.521 --> 23:57.784
And who wasn't.

23:57.827 --> 24:00.047
He never admitted it,

24:00.090 --> 24:03.137
but I think Morris
was working for Q.

24:03.180 --> 24:05.008
That's why I followed him
to the next gig.

24:05.052 --> 24:07.184
Do you still consider yourself
a believer of Q?

24:07.228 --> 24:10.318
Well, some stuff
didn't come true.

24:10.361 --> 24:12.451
The London bombing,
the Pope's arrest,

24:12.494 --> 24:13.843
Zuckerberg still has a job.

24:13.887 --> 24:15.584
January 20th
came and went,

24:15.628 --> 24:17.717
March 4th came and went.

24:17.760 --> 24:20.502
I'm starting to think Kennedy
is still dead.

24:20.546 --> 24:21.634
Both of them.

24:21.677 --> 24:22.939
Mm.

24:22.983 --> 24:25.942
So you don't believe
in Q anymore?

24:25.986 --> 24:27.683
Oh, I believe every word.

24:27.727 --> 24:29.206
Connor was, um --

24:29.250 --> 24:31.078
Deranged?

24:31.121 --> 24:33.515
Let's say...
reality-challenged,

24:33.559 --> 24:35.299
which doesn't make him
a killer.

24:35.343 --> 24:38.085
No. And the fact that he had
a camera on his shoulder

24:38.128 --> 24:39.956
for the entire
murder window

24:40.000 --> 24:41.958
means that he couldn't
have killed Morris,

24:42.002 --> 24:44.091
so we were back
to square one.

24:44.134 --> 24:45.919
Interviewer: When the QAnon lead
didn't pan out,

24:45.962 --> 24:47.747
how did you pick up
the pieces of the case?

24:47.790 --> 24:50.489
We rolled up our sleeves
and put in the hours.

24:50.532 --> 24:52.012
We took on
the painstaking process

24:52.055 --> 24:54.754
of reviewing
every piece of video Morris shot

24:54.797 --> 24:56.233
in the weeks
before he died,

24:56.277 --> 25:00.237
including the footage
Yvonne "forgot" to give us.

25:00.281 --> 25:02.065
Until I found something
that changed everything.

25:04.633 --> 25:06.809
Lopez!

25:06.853 --> 25:08.376
Come look at this!

25:08.419 --> 25:10.073
So I immediately informed
Detective Lopez

25:10.117 --> 25:11.031
of what I discovered.

25:11.074 --> 25:11.814
Look what I just found.

25:11.858 --> 25:13.250
Wow.

25:13.294 --> 25:14.251
What?

25:14.295 --> 25:16.123
Look.

25:16.166 --> 25:17.820
Morris: Okay.

25:23.522 --> 25:26.176
I thought I knew everything
about Patrick's murder.

25:26.220 --> 25:28.483
I had done my homework.

25:28.527 --> 25:32.922
But the truth was hiding right
in front of me all this time.

25:32.966 --> 25:35.969
I know
who killed Patrick Hayes.

25:36.012 --> 25:37.144
And I can prove it. I --

25:40.103 --> 25:41.104
Uh, someone's here.

25:42.541 --> 25:43.716
More to follow.

25:43.759 --> 25:45.108
Nolan: That video
was recorded

25:45.152 --> 25:47.023
minutes before
Morris was murdered.

25:51.288 --> 25:53.726
Interviewer: I mean, Morris
claiming that he knew

25:53.769 --> 25:54.988
who the killer was
must've been energizing for you.

25:55.031 --> 25:55.989
Finally. A break
in your roommate's murder --

25:56.032 --> 25:58.339
No, he --
He wasn't my roommate.

25:58.382 --> 26:00.820
And I -- I hate when people
call him that --

26:00.863 --> 26:02.343
you know, like we found
each other

26:02.386 --> 26:04.737
on some French Craigslist
or something like that.

26:04.780 --> 26:06.086
Patrick was my best friend,

26:06.129 --> 26:07.566
from the time
that we were little kids.

26:07.609 --> 26:08.828
I mean, I was at his house
so often,

26:08.871 --> 26:10.656
his dad bought us
two of everything,

26:10.699 --> 26:11.961
you know, like siblings.

26:12.005 --> 26:13.746
Yeah,
Patrick was my brother.

26:13.789 --> 26:15.182
How did it feel to hear
that Morris thought

26:15.225 --> 26:17.053
he'd discovered
who killed Patrick?

26:17.097 --> 26:21.405
I mean, there had been
so many theories over the years.

26:21.449 --> 26:24.147
And so many people think
that they had it figured out.

26:24.191 --> 26:27.716
I -- I just never really
got my hopes up about it.

26:27.760 --> 26:29.500
This was different, though.
I mean, he made a break

26:29.544 --> 26:30.850
in the case
and died minutes later.

26:30.893 --> 26:32.765
You have to see
the connection.

26:32.808 --> 26:37.160
Well, uh, in the words
of Detective Harper --

26:37.204 --> 26:40.294
We look for facts,
not stories.

26:40.337 --> 26:41.991
Yeah, sure, but, I mean,
the timing --

26:42.035 --> 26:44.167
I mean, these murders
had to be related.

26:44.211 --> 26:46.648
Whoever killed Patrick
also killed Morris.

26:46.692 --> 26:47.910
Interviewer: Is it possible
Morris found out

26:47.954 --> 26:49.651
that Aaron was the killer
all along?

26:49.695 --> 26:51.174
Not a chance.
The Paris police

26:51.218 --> 26:54.700
never had a shred of evidence
against Aaron.

26:54.743 --> 26:56.397
They fumbled
the entire case.

26:56.440 --> 26:57.703
Right off the bat,
the paparazzi

26:57.746 --> 26:59.487
completely contaminated
the crime scene.

27:16.722 --> 27:18.811
Interviewer: But Aaron's DNA
was all over the murder weapon.

27:18.854 --> 27:20.421
You mean the knife
the killer pulled

27:20.464 --> 27:22.858
from the kitchen block
on Aaron and Patrick's counter?

27:22.902 --> 27:25.426
What -- What do you want to bet
that if we went to your house,

27:25.469 --> 27:27.602
we'd find your DNA
all over your stuff, too?

27:27.646 --> 27:29.909
I mean --

27:29.952 --> 27:31.345
Was that too mean?

27:31.388 --> 27:33.956
No, that actually
felt good.

27:34.000 --> 27:35.523
It was a dumb question.

27:35.566 --> 27:37.046
From the beginning,
the French police's case

27:37.090 --> 27:38.700
against Aaron
seemed flawed --

27:38.744 --> 27:40.702
Oh, yeah.
Their case was a mess --

27:40.746 --> 27:43.270
and their forensics
were compromised.

27:43.313 --> 27:45.707
I mean, the theory
that Aaron killed Patrick

27:45.751 --> 27:47.970
because he didn't do his share
of the chores never made sense.

27:48.014 --> 27:50.059
For one thing,
they had a housekeeper.

27:50.103 --> 27:51.626
For another,
Aaron is not a psychopath,

27:51.670 --> 27:53.454
which you would have to be
to stab your roommate

27:53.497 --> 27:55.586
for leaving dirty dishes
in the sink.

27:55.630 --> 27:59.068
I mean, I've come close to
stabbing him over dirty dishes,

27:59.112 --> 28:01.636
but that's different --
we're married.

28:01.680 --> 28:02.898
Mm.

28:02.942 --> 28:04.204
Interviewer: What do you say
to the theory

28:04.247 --> 28:06.249
that Aaron had a falling out
with his roommate?

28:06.293 --> 28:08.991
Aaron and Patrick
were out partying that night.

28:09.035 --> 28:10.689
Does that sound like
a broken friendship

28:10.732 --> 28:12.299
careening towards murder?

28:12.342 --> 28:14.518
By his own admission, Aaron was
taking prescription drugs.

28:14.562 --> 28:17.391
Yeah. For a football injury
he got in high school.

28:17.434 --> 28:20.611
They impair your ability
to operate heavy machinery,

28:20.655 --> 28:23.397
not -- not turn you
into a hardened killer.

28:24.659 --> 28:27.009
Aaron passed out early.

28:27.053 --> 28:28.228
Woke up in the middle
of the night.

28:28.271 --> 28:31.753
Went to pee
and found Patrick's body.

28:41.067 --> 28:43.765
The French police took one look
at a young Black man,

28:43.809 --> 28:45.680
and decided he was the killer.

28:45.724 --> 28:48.161
I mean, they didn't even pursue
any other suspects.

28:48.204 --> 28:49.858
Bonjour, I appreciate you
speaking with me.

28:49.902 --> 28:52.252
Your accent
is terrible.

28:52.295 --> 28:53.644
Um, Detective,
you've been accused

28:53.688 --> 28:55.995
of leading an incredibly biased
investigation --

28:56.038 --> 28:57.779
<i>Mais non.</i>

28:57.823 --> 28:59.259
We followed the facts.

28:59.302 --> 29:01.217
Mm. And the fact
that Patrick picked up

29:01.261 --> 29:02.697
a woman at the club
that night?

29:02.741 --> 29:03.959
Collette Lavinge?

29:04.003 --> 29:06.614
She was seen leaving
the apartment

29:06.657 --> 29:08.094
before the time of death.

29:08.137 --> 29:09.443
Understand?

29:09.486 --> 29:11.662
What about her jealous,
controlling boyfriend?

29:11.706 --> 29:12.838
Did you interview him?

29:15.144 --> 29:17.756
- No. We did not.
- Mm.

29:17.799 --> 29:19.235
Interviewer: But the thing that
ultimately got you released

29:19.279 --> 29:21.934
from prison was the
identification of this man.

29:21.977 --> 29:23.326
Aaron: Yeah.
Collette's boyfriend, Julien.

29:23.370 --> 29:25.938
Handsome. French.

29:25.981 --> 29:27.678
And, you know,
let's just say it --

29:27.722 --> 29:29.289
he's super white.
You know?

29:29.332 --> 29:30.899
Uh, what is --

29:30.943 --> 29:33.293
What is "Finance Bro"
in French?

29:33.336 --> 29:35.817
Shouldn't you know that?
You spent years in France.

29:35.861 --> 29:38.080
Yeah, but I didn't --
I didn't retain it.

29:38.124 --> 29:41.214
It was actually a group
of Internet sleuths

29:41.257 --> 29:42.998
who found
Collette's boyfriend.

29:43.042 --> 29:46.349
They spent countless hours
investigating Aaron's case.

29:46.393 --> 29:48.090
They also pointed
the finger at dozens

29:48.134 --> 29:49.788
of innocent people,
ruining their lives.

29:49.831 --> 29:52.834
Yes. Some members of the group
took it a little too far.

29:52.878 --> 29:55.445
Interviewer:
We've been looking at the
Internet sleuths, actually.

29:55.489 --> 29:59.188
Any chance you post under
the title "truecrimejunkie"?

30:00.233 --> 30:01.190
I...

30:02.888 --> 30:05.629
That -- That --
That doesn't s--

30:05.673 --> 30:07.980
I might have logged on once --
once or twice, yeah.

30:08.023 --> 30:09.720
Seriously?

30:09.764 --> 30:11.635
I mean, can you not see
how people would take that

30:11.679 --> 30:13.115
as a clear sign of bias?

30:13.159 --> 30:17.032
I categorically deny any
preferential treatment, okay?

30:17.076 --> 30:18.294
Interviewer: How can you say
that with a straight face,

30:18.338 --> 30:19.861
when it was revealed that Julien
was the son

30:19.905 --> 30:21.515
of the French
Finance Minister?

30:21.558 --> 30:23.038
Are you telling me you didn't
get a phone call asking you --

30:23.865 --> 30:24.910
<i>Merci beaucoup.</i>

30:24.953 --> 30:26.215
<i>C'est terminé.</i>

30:26.259 --> 30:27.651
<i>Merci.</i>

30:27.695 --> 30:29.610
Oh, come on. Don't do that.
Come back.

30:29.653 --> 30:31.220
Interviewer: So, it must've been
so frustrating to learn

30:31.264 --> 30:33.092
that the French police
knew his identity

30:33.135 --> 30:35.877
before your first trial
and didn't say anything.

30:35.921 --> 30:37.313
I mean, yeah.
The -- The good news

30:37.357 --> 30:40.621
was that the fact
that they ignored Julien --

30:40.664 --> 30:42.884
uh, it got me my retrial.

30:42.928 --> 30:47.584
But the bad news was the
unidentified DNA on the knife --

30:47.628 --> 30:49.021
it -- it didn't belong
to Julien.

30:49.064 --> 30:51.240
So he --
You know, he had an alibi.

30:51.284 --> 30:52.720
As horrible
as the experience was,

30:52.763 --> 30:54.678
is there anything that you
actually miss from that time?

30:54.722 --> 30:56.202
I miss?

30:56.245 --> 30:57.159
God, no.

30:57.203 --> 30:59.335
W--

30:59.379 --> 31:00.902
Well, Carlos.

31:00.946 --> 31:01.947
Carlos?

31:01.990 --> 31:02.861
Yeah.

31:02.904 --> 31:05.080
Uh, Carlos the Jackal.

31:05.124 --> 31:06.908
He -- He was my cellmate.

31:06.952 --> 31:09.693
And, uh, man, pbht,
he has some stories.

31:09.737 --> 31:11.608
So you're saying the Jackal
got you through

31:11.652 --> 31:13.262
your year and a half
of incarceration?

31:13.306 --> 31:14.481
No.

31:14.524 --> 31:15.482
My mom did.

31:15.525 --> 31:17.353
Yeah, I don't --

31:17.397 --> 31:19.399
I don't think I would have got
through it without her.

31:19.442 --> 31:20.791
Um...

31:20.835 --> 31:24.534
She actually leased an apartment
in Paris

31:24.578 --> 31:26.014
until I was released.

31:26.058 --> 31:28.321
And, uh, she visited me
every week.

31:28.364 --> 31:30.192
And I'll tell you what.
If they would have let her,

31:30.236 --> 31:31.280
she would have been over there
every day.

31:31.324 --> 31:32.891
Of course I moved to Paris.

31:32.934 --> 31:34.370
I'm his mother.

31:34.414 --> 31:36.938
I would have served the prison
time for him if I could.

31:36.982 --> 31:38.113
You're a close family.

31:38.157 --> 31:39.114
We are.

31:39.158 --> 31:40.637
We've been tested.

31:40.681 --> 31:42.378
Were you close
with Patrick?

31:42.422 --> 31:43.553
Yes.

31:43.597 --> 31:44.859
I adored him.

31:44.903 --> 31:46.469
He was a wonderful boy.

31:46.513 --> 31:47.688
According
to your friends,

31:47.731 --> 31:48.732
you thought Patrick
was a troublemaker,

31:48.776 --> 31:49.951
and a bad influence
on Aaron.

31:49.995 --> 31:52.258
Anyone who said that
was lying.

31:52.301 --> 31:55.565
Yvonne -- were you in Paris
the day Patrick was murdered?

31:56.827 --> 31:59.656
Of course not.
I was here in LA.

31:59.700 --> 32:01.006
How do you explain
this footage,

32:01.049 --> 32:02.964
taken the day
of Patrick's murder?

32:11.103 --> 32:12.495
Oh, hell, no.

32:12.539 --> 32:13.627
This interview is over.

32:13.670 --> 32:15.585
Yvonne.
No. No.

32:15.629 --> 32:17.544
We did not okay
this question.

32:17.587 --> 32:19.372
Who do you think you are?

32:19.415 --> 32:20.721
Fired!

32:20.764 --> 32:21.635
I actually don't work
for you.

32:21.678 --> 32:22.418
You need to kiss my ass.

32:26.248 --> 32:28.468
Interviewer: Did you know
that your mother was in Paris

32:28.511 --> 32:29.164
the day that
Patrick was killed?

32:29.208 --> 32:30.905
What?

32:30.949 --> 32:33.255
No, she was --
she was home in LA.

32:33.299 --> 32:35.127
Mm. We have footage
of her shopping

32:35.170 --> 32:37.172
on the Champs-Elysées
the night of the murder.

32:37.216 --> 32:39.522
Okay, well, that --
That's impossible.

32:39.566 --> 32:40.697
Isn't this her?

32:50.533 --> 32:51.578
Okay.

32:53.493 --> 32:55.190
Officer Thorsen,
come back.

32:55.234 --> 32:57.584
Come on.
Let's finish this interview.

32:57.627 --> 32:59.673
Man:
Hey, there he is.

32:59.716 --> 33:00.935
- Aaron: You lied to me.
- Jimmy, get down.

33:00.979 --> 33:02.415
You lied to everyone.

33:02.458 --> 33:04.112
I didn't want all
my private business out there

33:04.156 --> 33:05.374
for all the world
to see.

33:05.418 --> 33:07.072
Mom, you are literally producing

33:07.115 --> 33:08.464
a reality show
about our lives.

33:08.508 --> 33:10.162
That's different.

33:10.205 --> 33:12.381
I was on trial for murder,
fighting for my life.

33:12.425 --> 33:13.730
Exactly.

33:13.774 --> 33:16.037
The fact that I was even
in Paris on that night --

33:16.081 --> 33:17.299
how does that help you?

33:17.343 --> 33:18.431
Interviewer: And what was
your reaction

33:18.474 --> 33:19.693
to the revelation
that Aaron's mother

33:19.736 --> 33:21.173
was in Paris at the time
of the murder?

33:21.216 --> 33:23.044
Like, bombshell.
Game changer.

33:23.088 --> 33:25.438
I mean, none of this stuff came
out at the time of the trial.

33:25.481 --> 33:26.787
This is --

33:26.830 --> 33:28.789
It's so exciting,
what it means for the case --

33:28.832 --> 33:31.052
Not for Aaron.
His mom lied to him.

33:31.096 --> 33:33.620
Y-Yes, that --
Well, that is true.

33:36.536 --> 33:37.841
Thanks for coming back in.

33:37.885 --> 33:39.191
We just need
to clear something up

33:39.234 --> 33:40.627
about the night Patrick
was killed.

33:40.670 --> 33:43.412
Patrick? I thought this was
about Morris's murder.

33:43.456 --> 33:45.284
Oh, it's about both.

33:45.327 --> 33:48.765
See, you felt Patrick
was a bad influence on your son.

33:48.809 --> 33:50.941
So you flew Aaron to Paris
to separate them.

33:50.985 --> 33:53.466
Only Patrick
followed Aaron there,

33:53.509 --> 33:55.642
so you took matters
into your own hands.

33:55.685 --> 33:57.948
You flew to Paris,
you killed Patrick.

33:57.992 --> 33:59.863
But somehow Morris
found out,

33:59.907 --> 34:02.475
so to keep
your deadly secret,

34:02.518 --> 34:03.911
you killed him too.

34:05.434 --> 34:09.003
Yeah,
that's a fun theory --

34:09.047 --> 34:11.484
a good story --
but you're wrong.

34:11.527 --> 34:13.225
Then explain
why you went to Paris

34:13.268 --> 34:15.183
and why you kept it
a secret.

34:15.227 --> 34:18.360
Because I was
with Jean-Pierre Darby.

34:18.404 --> 34:19.927
Who?
The footballer?

34:19.970 --> 34:23.322
Yes, we met a month before,
at a fashion show in Milan.

34:23.365 --> 34:24.671
I'm -- I'm sorry.

34:24.714 --> 34:27.195
You went to Paris for an
international bootie call?

34:27.239 --> 34:28.283
Yes.

34:28.327 --> 34:29.937
And we were in bed
all night.

34:29.980 --> 34:31.286
Ask him.

34:31.330 --> 34:33.854
Hell, ask the neighbors.

34:33.897 --> 34:35.986
Yvonne: They were determined
to convict you.

34:36.030 --> 34:37.988
Had it come out
that I was in town,

34:38.032 --> 34:39.555
they would've used it
against you,

34:39.599 --> 34:42.341
said that we were conspiring
to kill Patrick.

34:42.384 --> 34:45.518
Coming clean would've only hurt
your case, made it worse.

34:45.561 --> 34:47.911
Yeah, you know what? I forgot
how good you are at that.

34:47.955 --> 34:48.738
At what?

34:48.782 --> 34:50.914
At justifying yourself.

34:50.958 --> 34:53.830
You lied in a murder trial,
you cheated on your husband,

34:53.874 --> 34:56.006
and now you're the hero,
right?

34:56.050 --> 34:57.399
Yeah. Sure, Mom.

34:57.443 --> 34:58.531
We'll go with that.

35:03.927 --> 35:05.451
Interviewer: You accused Aaron's
mother of the murder.

35:05.494 --> 35:07.366
With almost no evidence
to back it up.

35:07.409 --> 35:08.628
I -- I did.

35:08.671 --> 35:11.935
And, uh, in my defense,

35:11.979 --> 35:14.068
I'd been scrubbing
reality show footage

35:14.112 --> 35:15.939
for over 200 hours
at that point.

35:15.983 --> 35:17.550
So who broke the case?

35:17.593 --> 35:19.029
Oh, that was
Detective Lopez.

35:19.073 --> 35:21.119
My wife is a badass.

35:21.162 --> 35:22.685
We knew the murders
were connected.

35:22.729 --> 35:24.383
And we knew that
Patrick's murder in Paris

35:24.426 --> 35:25.732
was never
properly investigated.

35:25.775 --> 35:28.169
So I dug
back into that case.

35:28.213 --> 35:30.302
Right now I'm just trying
to build a timeline,

35:30.345 --> 35:32.913
getting to know more
about Patrick's life.

35:32.956 --> 35:35.089
What did the four of you do
that last month?

35:35.133 --> 35:36.395
No detail is too small.

35:36.438 --> 35:38.484
Um...

35:38.527 --> 35:41.182
Let's ask my brain.

35:41.226 --> 35:43.271
I can tell you one thing
that we definitely didn't do.

35:43.315 --> 35:44.751
Go to class.

35:44.794 --> 35:46.796
I mean, Aaron's parents
let him borrow their private jet

35:46.840 --> 35:48.885
anytime he wanted,
so we went all around Europe.

35:48.929 --> 35:51.410
I mean, Italy.

35:51.453 --> 35:52.411
Greece.

35:52.454 --> 35:53.238
French Riviera.

35:54.326 --> 35:55.109
Can I see?

35:55.153 --> 35:56.545
Yeah.

35:56.589 --> 35:58.243
I thought --
screw school,

35:58.286 --> 36:00.462
when am I ever gonna get to
visit planet rich again, right?

36:00.506 --> 36:03.248
So, Santorini
for the weekend?

36:03.291 --> 36:04.423
Yes, please.

36:04.466 --> 36:06.164
These photos of you guys
on the tarmac,

36:06.207 --> 36:08.078
you always have
so much luggage.

36:08.122 --> 36:09.384
I know.

36:09.428 --> 36:11.865
Rowan always acted like
it was the Oregon Trail.

36:11.908 --> 36:13.475
Why?
Every time I've seen him,

36:13.519 --> 36:15.347
he was wearing a golf tee
and jeans.

36:15.390 --> 36:16.783
Not exactly
a clotheshorse.

36:16.826 --> 36:19.264
Oh, uh...

36:19.307 --> 36:20.482
True.

